Among the Iewes there were peculiar Officers, Deut. 1. 15. Car. Sig. de Rep, Heb. l. 7. 6. 7. (significantly entitled by the Septuagint 
                  〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
               ) who were commissioned to admit or reject all causes; without whose approbation, and recommendation to the Iudges, none were allowed to be determined.
